208: The last filter in the filter chain is router filter. The router filter calls
209: UpstreamRequest::encodeMetadata(const MetadataMapVector& metadata\_map\_vector)
210: to pass the metadata to the codec, and the codec encodes and forwards the
211: metadata to the upstream. If the connection to the upstream has not been
212: established when metadata is received, the metadata is temporarily stored in
213: UpstreamRequest::downstream\_metadata\_map\_vector\_. When the connection is
214: ready (UpstreamRequest::onPoolReady()), the metadata is then passed to the codec
215: and forwarded to the upstream.
216: 
217: Envoy can also add new request metadata through filters's decoding interfaces
218: (See section [Inserting metadata](#inserting-metadata) for detailed interfaces).
